<div id="review_322297145" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/322297145" />
    <a title="Randy Alcorn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9199254-randy-alcorn"><img alt="Randy Alcorn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442438978p2/9199254.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/322297145?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Randy Alcorn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Randy Alcorn" href="/user/show/9199254-randy-alcorn">Randy Alcorn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9199254-randy-alcorn?shelf=writing">writing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9199254-randy-alcorn?shelf=christian-life">christian-life</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer322297145" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2669021550464019672">I read many books, but seldom do I enjoy one more than I did Tony Reinke&apos;s A Christian Guide to Reading Books. Many of my greatest childhood adventures, and much of my growth after I was converted as a teenager, came through reading imagination-expanding and life-changing books. Tony&apos;s writing is thoughtful, perceptive, concise, and God-honoring. He honors biblical authority, and offers helpful guidance, while allowing for a variety of tastes. A Christian Guide to Reading Books rings true to my </span>
  <span id="freeText2669021550464019672" style="display:none">I read many books, but seldom do I enjoy one more than I did Tony Reinke's A Christian Guide to Reading Books. Many of my greatest childhood adventures, and much of my growth after I was converted as a teenager, came through reading imagination-expanding and life-changing books. Tony's writing is thoughtful, perceptive, concise, and God-honoring. He honors biblical authority, and offers helpful guidance, while allowing for a variety of tastes. A Christian Guide to Reading Books rings true to my own lifetime of reading experience. As a reader and writer of both nonfiction and fiction, I appreciate the breadth of Tony's treatment, which includes a variety of genres. For book lovers, this is a treasure and delight. For those who aren't book lovers, it makes a great case for becoming one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2669021550464019672" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


