<span id="freeTextContainer17076499521217490921">Lit! is a very helpful book for Christian readers who want to grow in their reading. I was glad the author placed reading Scripture as most important. I especially enjoyed the section on prioritizing what you read. I don’t have that much time and I want to read all the books, so I plan on using his tips for picking which books to read in the next year. As I read this book I thought to myself that in all my reading years I wasn’t taught how to be a productive or thoughtful reader. That needs to b</span>
  <span id="freeText17076499521217490921" style="display:none">Lit! is a very helpful book for Christian readers who want to grow in their reading. I was glad the author placed reading Scripture as most important. I especially enjoyed the section on prioritizing what you read. I don’t have that much time and I want to read all the books, so I plan on using his tips for picking which books to read in the next year. As I read this book I thought to myself that in all my reading years I wasn’t taught how to be a productive or thoughtful reader. That needs to be part of school curriculum! The book was very relatable and sectioned out well. I highlighted so many places and will definitely use it as a resource.</span>
