  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3374139384" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3374139384" />
    <a title="Jessica Perteet" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32775479-jessica-perteet"><img alt="Jessica Perteet" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613045728p2/32775479.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3374139384?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica Perteet" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica Perteet" href="/user/show/32775479-jessica-perteet">Jessica Perteet</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3374139384" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16385779056036865591">This book convicted me many times. He talks about signs of a mature reader. He talked about his main purpose for reading a book. He talked about having a theology for reading books as a Christian. He has a suggested yearly scheduled for reading great theologians that was very helpful. He finished with talking about books not being an idol or placing literature at too high a value. Great read.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


