<span id="freeTextContainer5905002680480454542">This book is a masterpiece - seriously. It&apos;s taken me forever to get through it, not because it&apos;s hard to read, but because I keep letting it get buried in my pile of books to read. Not anymore! I finally sat down and finished it off this afternoon - and it&apos;s genius. There is so much wisdom packed into these 200 odd pages, and as a Christian reader of books, I needed this. If you are a Christian you need this - regardless of whether you are a book dragon (aka moi) or a non-bookish-creature (thos</span>
  <span id="freeText5905002680480454542" style="display:none">This book is a masterpiece - seriously. It's taken me forever to get through it, not because it's hard to read, but because I keep letting it get buried in my pile of books to read. Not anymore! I finally sat down and finished it off this afternoon - and it's genius. There is so much wisdom packed into these 200 odd pages, and as a Christian reader of books, I needed this. If you are a Christian you need this - regardless of whether you are a book dragon (aka moi) or a non-bookish-creature (those unfortunate people xD). This is a book that I'll be coming back to again and again, as I feel that I will need to be reminded of the truths contained in it often! Why Christians should read, what Christians should read, how Christians should read - it's got everything covered. And it's covered in such a readable, healthy, Biblical fashion... well it's just amazing. This deserves 5 and more stars and it's going on my list of 'very highly recommended books'</span>
