  <span id="freeText12269629194802326594" style="display:none">According to Reinke, an efficient adult will probably be able to read only 2,600 books over 50 years - an incredibly small number given the volume of published works available. He creates a solid framework for discerning which books are worth reading and how to prioritize them. I was also struck by his emphasizing the written word over other forms of media - God communicates to us through writing, and it is through words that we are able to fully understand reality. After reading this guide, I would like to reframe my reading list to prioritize theology, begin reading in the mornings and afternoons (in addition to the evenings), and start annotating my books.</span>
